1 a. Administer an appraiser panel.
2 b. Recruit, retain, or select appraisers.
3 c. Qualify, verify licensing or certification, and negotiate fees and service level
4 expectations with persons who are part of an appraiser panel.
5 d. Contract with appraisers to perform appraisal assignments.
6 e. Receive an order for an appraisal from one person, and deliver the order for the
7 appraisal to an appraiser that is part of an appraiser panel for completion.
8 f. Manage the process of having an appraisal performed, including providing
9 administrative duties, such as receiving appraisal orders and reports, submitting
10 completed appraisal reports to creditors and underwriters, collecting fees from
11 creditors and underwriters for services provided, and reimbursing appraisers for
12 services performed.
13 g. Track and determine the status of appraisal orders.
14 h. Conduct an appraisal review or other quality control of a completed appraisal
15 prior to the delivery of the appraisal to the person that ordered the appraisal.
16 i. Provide a completed appraisal performed by an appraiser to one or more clients.
17 4. "Appraisal review" means the act or process of developing and communicating an
18 opinion about the quality of another appraiser's work that was performed as part of an
19 appraisal assignment related to the appraiser's data collection, analysis, opinions,
20 conclusions, estimate of value, or compliance with the uniform standards of
21 professional appraisal practice. This term does not include:
22 a. A general examination for grammatical, typographical, or other similar errors.
23 b. A general examination for completeness, including regulatory client requirements,
24 or both, as specified in the agreement process that does not communicate an
25 opinion.
26 5. "Appraiser panel" means a network of licensed or certified appraisers who have:
27 a. Responded to an invitation, request, or solicitation from an appraisal
28 management company, in any form, to perform appraisals for persons that have
29 ordered appraisals through the appraisal management company, or to perform
30 appraisals for the appraisal management company directly, on a periodic basis,
31 as requested and assigned by the appraisal management company.
