6 SECTION 2. AMENDMENT. Section 43-23.5-07 of the North Dakota Century Code is
7 amended and reenacted as follows:
8 43-23.5-07. Exemptions.
9 The provisions of this chapter do not apply to:
10 1. An appraisal firm.
11 2. A federally regulated appraisal management company, or a financial institution,
12 including a department or unit within the institution, that is regulated by an agency of
13 this state or the United States government.
14 3. A person that enters an agreement with an appraiser for the performance of an
15 appraisal that upon completion results in a report signed by both the appraiser who
16 completed the appraisal and the appraiser who requested completion of the appraisal.
17 4. An appraisal management company with an appraisal panel of fewer than sixteen
18 certified or licensed appraisers in this state or fewer than twenty-five nationally within a
19 given year.
20 5. An appraisal management company that is a subsidiary owned and controlled by a
21 financial institution that is subject to appraisal independence standards at least as
22 stringent as those under chapter 43-23.5-21, if regulated by an agency of this state, or
23 the Truth in Lending Act [15 U.S.C. 1601 et seq.], if regulated by the United States
24 government.
